01:37:11,110 --> 01:37:13,695
Sir, he says he's sorry about Wade.

1197
01:37:13,780 --> 01:37:15,822
He says he's sorry about Wade, sir.

1198
01:37:15,907 --> 01:37:17,574
Captain.

1199
01:37:17,700 --> 01:37:19,576
Captain, this isn't right.

1200
01:37:19,660 --> 01:37:23,205
You know this. He's a prisoner.
He surrendered.

1201
01:37:23,915 --> 01:37:25,874
He surrendered, sir!

1202
01:37:36,552 --> 01:37:38,261
Tell him

1203
01:37:40,264 --> 01:37:43,600
to march 1,000 paces in that direction,

1204
01:37:43,726 --> 01:37:44,935
then he can take off the blindfold.

1205
01:37:45,061 --> 01:37:46,103
We'll be gone, and he turns himself in

1206
01:37:46,229 --> 01:37:48,021
to the first Allied patrol
he comes across.

1207
01:37:48,106 --> 01:37:49,106
- Thank you, sir.
- REIBEN: You gotta be kidding me.

1208
01:37:49,232 --> 01:37:52,025
- We're letting him go?
- He's a POW, Reiben.

1209
01:37:52,110 --> 01:37:56,446
Can't take him with us.
Our guys'll pick him up sooner or later.

1210
01:38:07,125 --> 01:38:09,376
Only if he doesn't get picked up
by his own Wehrmacht first,

1211
01:38:09,460 --> 01:38:12,129
then thrown back into circulation.

1212
01:38:14,298 --> 01:38:16,716
Captain, you just let the enemy go.

1213
01:38:16,801 --> 01:38:19,719
- This is such bullshit.
- Y'all got that right.

1214
01:38:19,804 --> 01:38:21,805
Bullshit? Right. This is bullshit?

1215
01:38:21,931 --> 01:38:23,974
- Shooting a prisoner, that'd be okay?
- Upham, shut your mouth.

1216
